==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sycophantical
<hw>Syc`o*phan"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gr. <?/ slanderous.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to a sycophant; characteristic of a sycophant;
meanly or obsequiously flattering; courting favor by mean adulation;
parasitic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be cheated and ruined by a <qex>sycophantical</qex>
parasite.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sycophantic</qex> servants to the King of Spain.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sycophantish</ent>⟦br⟧
